  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A tort is a civil wrong — an act or omission that causes harm to another person and for which the law provides a remedy, typically monetary compensation. Tort law is distinct from criminal law: the state prosecutes crimes, but injured parties bring tort claims. The same act (an assault, for example) can be both a crime and a tort, prosecuted by the state and sued for by the victim.",
